In the trade sector IBM recently introduced the platform "Smarter Commerce" to help dealers manage the entire commercial cycle.
IBM also has a strong history in the Czech Republic.
In 1932 IBM founded a branch in Czechoslovakia at the time - as the first country in Central and Eastern Europe at all.
Today IBM ČR also operates a strategic outsourcing center in Brno.
The Central for Central and Eastern Europe is located in Prague and here is also a world-level top research team dealing with the technology of voting recognition.
